{# network-config — Netplan v2, gpu-h200 role (InfiniBand backend).

Differs from the RoCE roles (gpu-b300 / gpu-b200):
  - The 8 east-west NICs are InfiniBand HCA ports configured as IPoIB
    (ib0..ib7), one /24 per rail. MTU 2044 is the IPoIB datagram-mode
    default (connected mode can go higher, but is left out-of-band).
  - No `virtual-function-count`: InfiniBand RDMA is native to the HCA;
    there is no Soft-RoCE substrate and no Netplan-driven SR-IOV here.
  - IPoIB rails are NOT bonded — multi-rail collectives are handled by
    NCCL/UCX over the fabric, not by LACP.

WHY IPoIB sits under `ethernets:` — Netplan v2 has no first-class
`infinibands` key; networkd assigns IP to an IPoIB link the same way it
does an Ethernet link, so the `ethernets:` stanza is the supported path.

WHY match-by-macaddress on ib* is a placeholder — real ConnectX IPoIB
ports present a 20-byte hardware address / port GUID, not a 6-byte MAC.
The match is kept uniform with the Ethernet NICs for templating; on real
hardware substitute `match: {name: "ibp*s0"}` or a GUID-keyed udev/.link
rule. See docs/adr/0013-gpu-h200-infiniband-role.md.
#}
network:
  version: 2
  renderer: networkd

  ethernets:
{% for nic in ns_nics %}
    {{ nic.name }}:
      match:
        macaddress: {{ nic.mac }}
      set-name: {{ nic.name }}
      mtu: {{ nic.mtu }}
{% endfor %}
{% for nic in ib_underlays %}
    {{ nic.name }}:
      match:
        macaddress: {{ nic.mac }}
      set-name: {{ nic.name }}
      mtu: {{ nic.mtu }}
      addresses:
        - {{ nic.address }}
{% endfor %}

  bonds:
    {{ bond.name }}:
      interfaces:
{% for member in bond.members %}
        - {{ member }}
{% endfor %}
      mtu: {{ bond.mtu }}
      parameters:
        mode: {{ bond.mode }}
        lacp-rate: {{ bond.lacp_rate }}
        transmit-hash-policy: {{ bond.transmit_hash_policy }}

  vlans:
{% for vlan in vlans %}
    {{ vlan.name }}:
      id: {{ vlan.vlan_id }}
      link: {{ vlan.parent }}
      mtu: {{ vlan.mtu }}
      addresses:
        - {{ vlan.address }}
{% if vlan.gateway is not none %}
      routes:
        - to: default
          via: {{ vlan.gateway }}
{% endif %}
{% if vlan.dns %}
      nameservers:
        addresses:
{% for ns in vlan.dns %}
          - {{ ns }}
{% endfor %}
{% if vlan.search_domain is not none %}
        search:
          - {{ vlan.search_domain }}
{% endif %}
{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
